"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60652","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-18","<p>The Government is committed to turning the tide on fraudulent personal injury claims, and we have introduced a raft of measures to discourage unnecessary or frivolous claims and tackle inflated costs. Most recently, I announced on 9 June (Column 27WS)a number of steps that the Government intends to take to reduce the volume of fraudulent claims. These include the power for courts to dismiss fundamentally dishonest claims and a ban on lawyers offering inducements to bring personal injury claims.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2014-06-18T16:50:03.9397837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60652/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60652/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60652/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-09","Compensation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what steps he is taking to address any growth of a compensation culture in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","199674"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60653","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Department for Business, Innovation and Skills will continue to require students seeking maintenance loans to meet criteria includeing residency, type of course and place of study.</p><p> </p>","Havant","Mr David Willetts",,"2014-06-16T16:05:45.5554554Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60653/answer","Biography information for Lord Willetts","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60653/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60653/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2014-06-09","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what recent assessment he has made of the current eligibility criteria for higher education maintenance loans.","false","Biography information for Mr Aidan Burley","Cannock Chase","Mr Aidan Burley","199673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Thursday 12 June 2014]</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As stated in the impact assessment on the abolition of the Standards Board regime (published in January 2011), a post implementation review will be carried out three to five years after implementation of the policy which was in July 2012.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>My Department routinely receives representations about standards arrangements in local government, and indeed, on a whole range of local government issues. We will have regard to representations and comments when we undertake our post implementation review.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>However, Ministers are clear that the new provisions are a significant improvement on the old, discredited regime. The Localism Act has clarified predetermination rules allowing elected councillors to campaign and speak up on local issues. We have reversed the petty culture of malicious and unfounded complaints that wasted time and energy and undermined the good reputation of local government. We have increased transparency on councillors' interests, and put in place criminal sanctions for the very rare instances of corruption. This is complemented by the role of political parties in ensuring good conduct, the law of libel, and the ultimate sanction: the ballot box.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","199698 ; 199700","2014-06-23T14:14:17.0686118Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654/answer/previousversion/1100","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60654/answer/previousversion/1100",,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2014-06-09","Councillors: Conduct","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what representations his Department has received from (a) local authorities and (b) others on sanctions available to councils under the Localism Act 2011 where councillors have been found to have been in breach of the Code of Conduct under that Act.","false","Biography information for Hilary Benn","Leeds Central","Hilary Benn","199699"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2014-06-23","<p> </p><p><em>[Holding Reply: Thursday 12 June 2014]</em></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>As stated in the impact assessment on the abolition of the Standards Board regime (published in January 2011), a post implementation review will be carried out three to five years after implementation of the policy which was in July 2012.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>My Department routinely receives representations about standards arrangements in local government, and indeed, on a whole range of local government issues. We will have regard to representations and comments when we undertake our post implementation review.</p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>However, Ministers are clear that the new provisions are a significant improvement on the old, discredited regime. The Localism Act has clarified predetermination rules allowing elected councillors to campaign and speak up on local issues. We have reversed the petty culture of malicious and unfounded complaints that wasted time and energy and undermined the good reputation of local government. We have increased transparency on councillors' interests, and put in place criminal sanctions for the very rare instances of corruption. This is complemented by the role of political parties in ensuring good conduct, the law of libel, and the ultimate sanction: the ballot box.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","199698 ; 199699","2014-06-23T14:14:17.3029325Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655/answer","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655/answer/previousversion/1106","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60655/answer/previousversion/1106",,,