"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60769","Department of Health","false","2014-06-16","<p>We have provided £400 million to the National Health Service over four years from 2011 for carers to have breaks from their caring responsibilities.</p><p> </p><p>In the 2013 Spending Review, we announced the £3.8 billion Better Care Fund, which includes £130 millionfunding for carers' breaks for 2015-16.</p><p><strong> </strong></p><p>In 2015-16, East Lancashire Clinical Commissioning Group will receive £8.1 million from the Better Care Fund.</p><p> </p>","North Norfolk","Norman Lamb",,"2014-06-16T13:29:24.4395864Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60769/answer","Biography information for Norman Lamb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60769/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60769/answer",,,,,,,,"17","Health","Health","2014-06-09","Respite Care: Pendle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to improve respite care provisions in Pendle constituency.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","199652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60770","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Department has information broken down relating to the enforcement by the Driver and Vehicle Standards Agency (DVSA) for the most recent year. The following prohibitions were found in the year to March 2014, a) 710 in England, b) 62 in the North West and c) 37 in Lancashire. National totals for the previous 4 years were, 2013 – 720, 2012 – 663, 2011 – 1617, 2010 – 2364. The Department does not have the Police data for this offence at this time. Enforcement of Construction and Use regulations is a matter for both DVSA and the police.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-16T15:43:19.5793218Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60770/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60770/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60770/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","Motor Vehicles: Glass","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many vehicles have been found to be in breach of rules about tinted windows in (a) England, (b) the North West and (c) Lancashire in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","199661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60771","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>Failure to register a vehicle following the six-month exemption period is not an offence for which a fixed penalty notice can be issued. The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency instead writes to keepers of these vehicles offering them an out of court settlement where it appears that an offence has been committed, so that the matter may be resolved without court proceedings. The table below shows the amount of these out of court settlement letters issued in the last five financial years.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>YEAR</p><p> </p></td><td><p>NUMBER OF OCS ISSUED</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>09/10</p><p> </p></td><td><p>108</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>10/11</p><p> </p></td><td><p>83</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>11/12</p><p> </p></td><td><p>192</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>12/13</p><p> </p></td><td><p>59</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>13/14</p><p> </p></td><td><p>84</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p /> <p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p /><p /> <p>Since April 2014, 237 out of court settlement letters have been issued.</p><p />","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-16T15:38:12.1352111Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60771/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60771/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60771/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","Motor Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many fixed penalty notices were issued to drivers of vehicles registered in another country that should have been but were not registered in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","199650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60772","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) receives information on foreign registered vehicles from the police and other enforcement agencies, as well as from members of the public. Other ways of obtaining this information are currently being explored.</p><p> </p><p>The DVLA has been working with the police to pilot a new enforcement process. This involves the DVLA providing the police forces with registration numbers of foreign registered vehicles which may have overstayed the six- month exemption period and where the keepers have not complied with UK requirements. This information enables the four police forces involved to seize and impound vehicles that have overstayed, where appropriate. If the pilot is successful, the DVLA will explore the potential for extending it to more police forces.</p><p> </p><p>The DVLA is also working with other government agencies to establish what other data might be used to track and identify over staying foreign registered vehicles.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-16T15:39:03.5189675Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60772/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60772/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60772/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","Motor Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department has taken to improve the reliability of tracking methodologies for foreign (a) registered and (b) unregistered vehicles in the UK.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","199651"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60773","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The table below shows figures for the amount of vehicles registered by the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Agency (DVLA) that were previously registered elsewhere between 2009 and 2012.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong><strong><strong><strong></strong></strong></strong></strong><p>YEAR</p><strong><strong><strong><strong></strong></strong></strong></strong><p> </p></td><td><strong><strong><strong><strong></strong></strong></strong></strong><p>NUMBER OF VEHICLES</p><strong><strong><strong><strong></strong></strong></strong></strong><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2009</p><p> </p></td><td><p>65,060</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010</p><p> </p></td><td><p>62,373</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011</p><p> </p></td><td><p>58,379</p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012</p><p> </p></td><td><p>57,910</p><p> </p></td></tr></tbody></table><p /> <p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>Since 2013 the way that certain vehicle transactions are processed has changed and the data gathered about foreign registered vehicles is no longer readily available. In 2013, the DVLA processed 99,168 applications to register new and previously registered imported vehicles.</p><p /> <p> </p><p />","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-06-16T15:36:37.8074853Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60773/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60773/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60773/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","Motor Vehicles: Registration","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, for how many vehicles registered in another country applications were made to the Driver and Vehicle Licensing Authority to register them in the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","199649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60774","HM Treasury","false","2014-06-16","<p><strong>I refer the Right Honourable Member to my answers of 12 May (column 332W) and 13 May (column 529W). </strong><strong>The number of residential properties in the UK valued at more than £2 million was estimated before Budget 2012 to be around 55,000.</strong></p><p> </p><p><strong>The Treasury does not have a precise regional breakdown of properties worth over £2million. </strong></p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2014-06-16T14:49:02.5531514Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60774/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60774/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60774/answer",,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2014-06-09","Property: Taxation","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what estimate he has made of the total number of properties (a) in the UK and (b) in the Greater London region affected by a levy on a property's value of above a (i) £2 million and (ii) £5 million threshold.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jowell","Dulwich and West Norwood","Dame Tessa Jowell","199755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60775","Cabinet Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>The information requested falls within the responsibility of the UK Statistics Authority. I have asked the Authority to reply.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2014-06-16T10:04:34.2",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60775/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60775/answer","PQ 199795.pdf","ONS Letter to Member","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60775/answer",,,,,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2014-06-09","Average Earnings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what estimate he has made of average household earnings in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Sarah Teather","Brent Central","Sarah Teather","199795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60776","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p> </p><p>The following information on number of households capped (latest data March 2014) is available by Local Authority at :</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-march-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/benefit-cap-number-of-households-capped-to-march-2014</a></p><p> </p><p>Data is available on number of households capped (current and cumulative), amount capped, number of dependents and household type.</p><p> </p><p>Details on length of time capped is not available.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-06-16T11:46:27.8456502Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60776/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60776/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60776/answer",,,,,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-06-09","Housing Benefit: Brent","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many households in the London Borough of Brent are affected by the household benefit cap; what the composition of the households is; and what the length of time and amount capped by the household benefit cap is.","false","Biography information for Sarah Teather","Brent Central","Sarah Teather","199793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60777","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>The GCSE and GCE Awarding Organisations are leading on developing subject content for reformed design and technology qualifications. In carrying out this work, they are drawing closely on advice from subject organisations with design and technical expertise. The draft criteria that are developed will be formally consulted on and the evidence gathered will be used to review and finalise the content for the new design and technology qualifications.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-16T16:34:35.9683076Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60777/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60777/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60777/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Design: Curriculum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what account he plans to take of (a) design and (b) technical knowledge in the review of the GCSE/GCE examination course in design and technology.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199611"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60778","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Government is committed to raising the quality of teaching in all subjects, including Design and Technology (D&amp;T). Headteachers and teachers are best placed to make decisions about what professional development they require in order to meet the needs of their pupils and school. A network of Teaching Schools has been established to improve the capacity of schools to take the lead in the training and development of teachers and create more opportunities for peer-to-peer learning. The Teachers' Standards set a clear benchmark for the level of practice expected of all teachers, and provide a valuable tool to help headteachers and teachers identify and address development needs through regular appraisal.</p><p> </p><p>The D&amp;T expert subject group, set up to provide support to teachers implementing the new D&amp;T curriculum, comprises of leading professionals in D&amp;T who work to clarify the key areas on which teachers most need further support, identifying the topics that can present the greatest challenge when discussing with pupils. The group liaises with relevant specialists and providers to develop and produce new resources where necessary. DATA, in partnership with others, have developed a range of resources including an annotated programme of study, providing advice and explanatory notes on implementation.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-16T16:54:08.853111Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60778/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60778/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60778/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Design: Teachers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what continued professional development assistance is provided to design and technology teachers.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60779","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>The GCSE and GCE Awarding Organisations are leading on developing new design and technology GCSEs and A levels. They are ensuring that the content builds on and is in line with the revised design and technology national curriculum.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-16T16:32:58.1029595Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60779/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60779/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60779/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Design: Curriculum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, whether the review of design and technology GCSE/GCE examination specifications will bring those examinations in line with the revised national curriculum for design and technology.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60780","Department for Education","false","2014-06-18","<p>The main objective of the Your Life campaign is to increase the number of young people choosing A levels in maths or physics.</p><p>The campaign will be led by an independent organisation chaired by Edwina Dunn, and it will run for three years.</p><p>It will seek support and resources from leading employers and organisations. The Government has provided limited funds to establish a website and other set-up work.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-18T16:21:30.6526896Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60780/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60780/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60780/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Science: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the (a) objectives, (b) governance, (c) intended duration and (d) funding of the Your Life campaign are; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60781","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>Design and Technology (D&amp;T) is an important subject that can inspire young people to pursue careers in engineering and manufacturing. Ofsted's 2011 report ‘Meeting technological challenges' found:</p><p> </p><p>“Most pupils in the primary and secondary schools visited enjoyed designing and making products and gained much satisfaction in acquiring technical skills and in seeing their ideas take shape.”</p><p> </p><p>During the review of the national curriculum, the Government consulted industry representatives, such as Dyson and Royal Academy of Engineering, teachers, subject associations and D&amp;T specialists to ensure the new D&amp;T curriculum is relevant to the modern world. We have strengthened the technological aspects of the subject by including new and emerging technologies, placed greater emphasis on links with STEM subjects to provide a context for their practical application and we are also reforming D&amp;T GCSE and A levels to include more rigorous content and build on the changes made to the curriculum. The new qualifications will be more ambitious, with greater stretch for the most able and prepare young people better for the demands of employment and further study.</p><p> </p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-16T16:15:44.1706331Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60781/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60781/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60781/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Design: Curriculum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the status and importance of design and technology at Key Stage 3, Key Stage 4 and post-16; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199615"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60782","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>Progress 8 will be the headline secondary school performance measure from 2016. This will be based on qualifications which schools will begin teaching in the autumn term of 2014. The new performance measures aim to encourage schools to offer a broad and balanced curriculum that meets the needs of all pupils.</p><p> </p><p>More schools than ever are entering pupils for the English Baccalaureate, which encourages the study of science, a language and a humanities subject alongside maths and English.</p>","Yeovil","Mr David Laws",,"2014-06-16T14:42:23.6965746Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60782/answer","Biography information for Mr David Laws","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60782/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60782/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Secondary Education: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what assessment he has made of the effect of progress 8 performance measures since their introduction in secondary schools.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199613"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60783","Department for Education","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Department does not collect nor hold the data requested.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2014-06-16T16:44:16.6074497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60783/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60783/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60783/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2014-06-09","Design: Education","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools have (a) merged design and technology with art and design and (b) removed design and technology from their curriculum since 2010.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199614"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60784","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p>Officer Cadets at the Afghan National Army Officer Academy (ANAOA) in Afghanistan receive specific training on UN Security Council resolution 1325. This supports one of the ANAOA's core training objectives to: “Comply with Afghan National Army gender integration/equality and diversity policy”. The course covers international law, human rights and women's rights, Islamic attitudes (including towards women) and the rights of the family, focusing on the role and equality of women in contemporary Afghan society.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-06-17T16:02:25.6177636Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60784/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60784/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60784/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-09","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to the Answer of 1 July 2013, Official Report, column 395W, on Afghanistan, whether recruits at the Afghan National Army Officer Academy in Afghanistan will receive specific training on UN Security Council resolution 1325.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199667"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60785","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p>The UK currently provides six female mentors to the Afghan National Army Officer Academy's (ANAOA) female training platoon. One additional female mentor is involved in the wider training programme at the Academy.<br><br>Many of the mentor posts at the ANAOA are reserved for male Service personnel, owing to the cultural sensibilities of our Afghan partners. We will continue to seek opportunities to deploy females into other mentoring posts to demonstrate to the Afghan National Army (ANA) that Servicewomen are exemplars and can be employed across a wide range of roles. <br><br>In relation to gender-sensitive training, one of the ANAOA's core training objectives is: “Comply with ANA gender integration/equality and diversity policy”. The course covers international law, human rights and women's rights, Islamic attitudes (including towards women) and the rights of the family, focusing on the role and equality of women in contemporary Afghan society.</p>","Rayleigh and Wickford","Mr Mark Francois",,"2014-06-17T16:01:45.7315709Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60785/answer","Biography information for Mr Mark Francois","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60785/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60785/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-09","Afghanistan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many of the 90 UK personnel plan to provide mentoring and related support to the Afghan national army officer academy he expects (a) to be female and (b) to be able to provide gender-sensitive training.","false","Biography information for Sir Peter Luff","Mid Worcestershire","Sir Peter Luff","199610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60786","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>As first announced on 15 December 2010 (Official Report, column 102WS), HMS ILLUSTRIOUS will retire from service this year. No final decision has been made on the specific date.<br><br>HMS OCEAN will shortly finish her extensive refit and take over as the Royal Navy's Landing Platform Helicopter ship.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2014-06-17T15:59:28.5468141Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60786/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60786/answer","20101215 - Hansard extract SDSR Royal Navy.doc","Hansard extract on SDSR Royal Navy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60786/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-09","HMS Illustrious","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, for what reasons the planned out-of-service date for HMS Illustrious has been brought forward; what the new date is; and who took the decision to change that date.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","199753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60787","Ministry of Defence","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>There have been no such discussions with the Royal Canadian Navy or the United States Navy. However, we work closely with many nations and provide opportunities for their personnel to serve with the Royal Navy through a range of schemes including exchange and liaison postings.</p>","Broxtowe","Anna Soubry",,"2014-06-16T14:38:17.3393967Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60787/answer","Biography information for Anna Soubry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60787/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60787/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2014-06-09","HMS Sultan","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions he or officials in his Department have had with counterparts in the Royal Canadian Navy or the US Navy on personnel of those navies undertaking conversion training at HMS Sultan to fill current vacancies in suitably qualified and experienced personnel positions.","false","Biography information for Angus Robertson","Moray","Angus Robertson","199754"
