"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60812","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>To provide the full information as requested would risk compromising the privacy of the applicants. The following anonymised summary information may be helpful:</p><p> </p><p>For Phase One:</p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Carter Jonas has valued a total of 47 properties.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><ul><li>4 of those valuations have been queried by applicants.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Carter Jonas valuations have been used to form the offer price a total of 41 times and 35 of these offers have been accepted.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p> </p><p /><p /><p>For Phase Two :</p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Carter Jonas has valued a total of 22 properties.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><ul><li>None of those valuations have been queried by applicants.</li></ul></p><p> </p><p> </p><p><ul><li>Carter Jonas valuations have been used to form the offer price a total of 20 times and all of these offers have been accepted.</li></ul></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-12T14:40:38.7630911Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60812/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60812/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60812/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish a list of properties that have been valued by Carter Jonas under the Exceptional Hardship Scheme for High Speed 2; and whether those valuations have been accepted or queried by the owners of those properties.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199640"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60813","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>HS2 Ltd aims to respond to all enquiries as soon as possible and within a maximum of 20 working days.</p><p /> <p>Performance against this standard was 93% for April 2013 to March 2014.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p>A high proportion of these enquiries relate to property compensation but HS2 Ltd does not compile separate performance data for different enquiry types.</p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p> </p><p /> <p /><p /> <p /><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-12T14:45:05.2854939Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60813/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60813/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60813/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the average time taken to respond by HS2 Ltd to property related compensation enquiries is; and what the longest time taken to respond to such an enquiry has been.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199645"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60814","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>The complaints procedure, along with other aspects of the Residents' Charter for HS2, is currently being developed and further information will be published in due course.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-12T14:43:20.9862066Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60814/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60814/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60814/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people have accessed the HS2 Ltd complaints procedure set out in the HS2 Residents' Charter of April 2014; what the details are of each complaint; what the outcome is of each complaint; and what complaints are outstanding.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199644"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60815","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>Details of the Independent Residents Commissioner and Residents' Charter for HS2 are currently being developed and further information will be published in due course.</p><p> </p><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-12T14:41:53.1574328Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60815/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60815/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60815/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish details of the recruitment of the Independent Residents Commissioner promised by HS2 Ltd in the April 2014 HS2 Residents Charter, including (a) where this position is advertised, (b) the remuneration package offered, (c) the interview process and the interview panel members, (d) the estimated date of any appointments, (e) the Commissioner's powers and (f) how the Commissioner's independence will be assured.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60816","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>HS2 Ltd does not currently allocate case officers to residents affected by HS2 but refers their concerns to the appropriate specialist.　 　As stated in their leaflet ‘HS2 Residents' Charter',　HS2 Ltd will offer a single named case officer when the Charter　is developed. The leaflet can be viewed on the HS2 Ltd website or is available via HS2 Public Enquiries.</p><p> </p><p />","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-16T15:06:08.6219906Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60816/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60816/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60816/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will list the case officers allocated by HS2 Ltd to assist residents affected by High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60817","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The names of the property specialists for anyone seeking advice on compensation are published in the factsheet &quot;Your Guide to the HS2 Express Purchase Scheme&quot;. The factsheet can be viewed on the HS2 Ltd website or is available via HS2 Public Enquiries.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-06-16T15:08:47.0078432Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60817/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60817/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60817/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-09","High Speed 2 Railway Line","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will list the HS2 Ltd property specialists who are available for private meetings with residents who are affected by High Speed 2.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","199606"
