Zita chemical weapons attack on 11 April 2014.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","199738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60832","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-06-16","<p>We discuss the security of hydrocarbon sites at the UK-Algeria Strategic Security Partnership, which was established after In Amenas and met for the second time in November 2013. In this forum the National Security Advisor, Sir Kim Darroch, spoke to Algerian Prime Minister Abdelmalek Sellal, Foreign Minister Ramtane Lamamra and the Algerian military about this issue. I also discussed the importance of security at hydrocarbon sites with the then Algerian Deputy Foreign Minister Madjid Bouguerra during my visits to Algiers in both January and April 2014.</p>","Faversham and Mid Kent","Hugh Robertson",,"2014-06-16T10:22:38.8266556Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60832/answer","Biography information for Sir Hugh Robertson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60832/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60832/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-06-09","Algeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations he has made to the Algerian government to ensure the safety of UK oil and gas workers in the country; and who his primary point of contact in the office of the President of that country is in discussions on that matter.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","199744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60833","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2014-06-17","<p>In 2013, the UK imported 6,200 tonnes of crude oil from Algeria, and 4,500 GWh of gas. Total UK imports were 50,300 tonnes of crude oil and 525,000 GWh of gas. Data for 2013 are rounded to the nearest hundred and are provisional.</p><p> </p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2014-06-17T16:03:41.9621943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60833/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60833/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60833/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2014-06-09","Fossil Fuels: Algeria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much oil and gas was imported to the UK from Algeria in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mark Hendrick","199745"
