ty been at risk. There are no significant historical trends in the attached figures and it is fair to say that privately managed prisons achieve the majority of their contractual targets with proportionately low levels of performance points and financial remedies applied as a result. The data for each contract is closely monitored by MoJ staff and any emerging or sustained performance failures are discussed in detail with the relevant Contractor in order to rectify performance shortfalls as quickly as possible.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","199485 ; 199486 ; 199489 ; 199495","2014-06-16T11:42:56.9769935Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60488/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60488/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Dovegate Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what financial penalties have been incurred by Serco in relation to its contract to run HM Prison Dovegate since May 2010.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60489","Department for International Development","false","2014-06-16","<p> </p><p>The information necessary to provide a detailed response to your request is not held centrally and could only be obtained at a disproportionate cost. The information is spread across DFID and other government departments, and the data is not sufficiently disaggregated to report purely on the amount spent on construction of prisons.</p><p> </p>","Hornsey and Wood Green","Lynne Featherstone",,"2014-06-16T15:40:34.1097118Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60489/answer","Biography information for Baroness Featherstone","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60489/answer",,,,,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2014-06-06","Developing Countries: Prisons","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how much aid funding the UK has disbursed to support the construction of prisons in each country and in each year since 2008.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199510"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60490","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-16","<p>NOMS takes the issue of assaults very seriously. It currently has systems in place to deal with perpetrators quickly and robustly, with serious incidents referred to the police for prosecution. It is working closely with the police and CPS to develop a new joint protocol to report crimes in prison - this includes pushing for prosecutions when prison staff are attacked.</p><p> </p><p>The number of arrests and charges from assault incidents in prison can only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-16T11:19:11.4502105Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60490/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60490/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60490/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Prisons: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many reported incidents of violence inside prisons resulted in (a) an arrest and (b) a charge, by type of offence, in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199529"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60491","Home Office","false","2014-06-17","<p> </p><p>£5.4 million has been spent to date on the conversion of HM Prison The Verne into an Immigration Removal Centre.</p><p> </p>","Staffordshire Moorlands","Karen Bradley",,"2014-06-17T14:06:49.4060044Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60491/answer","Biography information for Karen Bradley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60491/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60491/answer",,,,,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2014-06-06","Verne Prison","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what the cost to the public purse has been of the conversion of HM Prison The Verne into an immigration removal centre.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199511"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60492","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-17","<p /> <p /> <p /> <p>We commissioned a fundamental review of release on temporary licence (ROTL) policy and practice last year and, in March, announced a package of measures to ensure that the public was properly protected. We have brought forward some of those measures so that they begin to take effect immediately; particularly with more serious offenders, where the review concluded that an enhanced risk assessment approach should be taken. These offenders must have their release agreed by the governor or deputy and the board considering release must have sight of a psychologist's case review report. Temporary licence is an important tool in preparing prisoners for release from prison but we must make sure it is done safely and that the public can feel confident in the risk assessment and monitoring arrangements.</p><p> </p><p>Data in relation to the main offence types for offenders released on temporary licence is recorded in the following categories:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Violence against the person</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Sexual offences</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Robbery</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Burglary</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Theft and handling</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fraud and forgery</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Drug offences</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Motoring offences</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Other offences</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Offence not recorded</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>It is therefore not possible to determine the number of offenders serving custodial sentences for serious violent and sexual assaults, who were released on temporary licence, <a target="_blank">without incurring disproportionate cost.</a></p><p> </p><p>Offenders convicted of offences within each of these categories, with the exception of motor offences, were released on temporary licence in each year between 2011 and 2013. Data for 2010 cannot be provided due to a database migration.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright","199532","2014-06-17T16:32:36.5441613Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60492/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60492/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60492/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Prisoners' Release","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prisoners released on temporary licence in (a) 2010, (b) 2011, (c) 2012 and (d) 2013 were serving custodial sentences for serious violent and sexual assaults.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199514"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60493","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-16","<p>The Incident Reporting System is used by establishments to record events that undermine the safety of those within an establishment and/or subvert the authority or effectiveness of the establishment's regimes or facilities.</p><p> </p><p>There is a range of incident types recorded on this system and the data needs to undergo validation and assurance before being published. To undertake this on each incident type that is reported takes time and so I will write to you when this information is available for the latest period.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-16T10:29:55.7884953Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60493/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60493/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60493/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Prisons: Discipline","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many incidents of each type were recorded on the Incident Reporting System in (a) privately and (b) publicly run prisons in each month since 1 January 2014.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199515"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60494","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-11","<p>The information requested is not held centrally.The National Probation Service and the Community Rehabilitation Companies did not exist on 1 May 2014, having come into existence on 1 June 2014. Prior to their existence, vacancies were managed locally by Probation Trusts, which have now ceased to exist.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-11T16:56:51.0403326Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60494/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60494/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60494/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Probation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many unfilled vacancies there were in (a) the National Probation Service and (b) each community rehabilitation company on 1 May 2014.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199516"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60495","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-06-16","<p>NOMS takes the issue of assaults very seriously. It currently has systems in place to deal with perpetrators quickly and robustly, with serious incidents referred to the police for prosecution. It is working with the police and <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Crown_Prosecution_Service" target="_blank">Crown Prosecution Service</a> to ensure that prisoners who assault staff are charged and punished appropriately.</p><p> </p><p>To protect the safety of prisoners and prison staff details of incidents by individual prisoners cannot be provided.</p><p> </p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2014-06-16T10:18:37.4274714Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60495/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60495/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/60495/answer",,,,,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-06-06","Prisons: Crimes of Violence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many reported incidents of assault by Kevin Thakrar on (a) prison officers and (b) other prisoners there were in each of the last four years; how many of those incidents were reported to the police; and in how many of those incidents did Crown Prosecution Service decide (i) not to prosecute and (ii) to prosecute.","false","Biography information for Sadiq Khan","Tooting","Sadiq Khan","199501"
