"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58298","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>The National Travel Survey (NTS) has trip data by mode of transport collected via a 7-day travel diary for residents of Great Britain. However, data are not available for specific local areas as the sample is too small at that level of geography to provide reliable results.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Some regional level results are available through combining two survey years of data together. The latest results available are for 2011 and 2012 combined. They cover all domestic journeys by all modes of transport, including car, rail and bus.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table NTS9903 (at link below) shows the average number of trips per person per year by region of residence.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259042/nts9903.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259042/nts9903.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table NTS9905 (at link below) shows the percentage of trips within and between regions.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259032/nts9905.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259032/nts9905.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","199403","2014-06-12T11:26:12.4348131Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58298/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58298/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58298/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-05","Travel: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on how many journeys were made between Portsmouth and Brighton by (a) car, (b) rail and (c) bus in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","199402"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58299","Department for Transport","false","2014-06-12","<p> </p><p>The National Travel Survey (NTS) has trip data by mode of transport collected via a 7-day travel diary for residents of Great Britain. However, data are not available for specific local areas as the sample is too small at that level of geography to provide reliable results.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Some regional level results are available through combining two survey years of data together. The latest results available are for 2011 and 2012 combined. They cover all domestic journeys by all modes of transport, including car, rail and bus.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table NTS9903 (at link below) shows the average number of trips per person per year by region of residence.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259042/nts9903.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259042/nts9903.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Table NTS9905 (at link below) shows the percentage of trips within and between regions.</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259032/nts9905.xls" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/259032/nts9905.xls</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","199402","2014-06-12T11:26:12.5370916Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58299/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58299/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58299/answer",,,,,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-06-05","Travel: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what information his Department holds on how many journeys were made between Southampton and Brighton by (a) car, (b) rail and (c) bus in each of the last five years for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Nicholas Soames","199403"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58300","Department for Culture Media and Sport","false","2014-06-12","<p>The Independent regulator and competition authority for the UK communications industries (Ofcom) publishes broadband coverage data for the UK; its 2013 UK fixed-line broadband performance report indicates the following average modem synchronisation speed for the Glasgow City, Scotland and the UK. Data by Constituency area is not available.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Average modem sync speed 2013 </strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Glasgow City</p></td><td><p>17.2 Mbit/s</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Scotland</p></td><td><p>15.8 Mbit/s</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK</p></td><td><p>17.6 Mbit/s</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2014-06-12T10:54:21.8992581Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58300/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58300/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/58300/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2014-06-05","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what estimate he has made of the average broadband speed in (a) Glasgow North West constituency, (b) Glasgow, (c) Scotland and (d) the UK.","false","Biography information for John Robertson","Glasgow North West","John Robertson","199154"
